{"answer":"No, Heather Collins cannot legally allow all her care staff to nap at the same time.

Under NYCRR §487.9(a)(15) (for Adult Homes), at least one individual currently qualified to administer basic first aid must be "on duty and onsite at all times." The operator must also provide staff "sufficient in number and qualified by training and experience to render, at a minimum, those services mandated by statute or regulation" (§487.9(a)(1)) and maintain written staffing schedules (§487.9(a)(6)). Allowing all staff to nap simultaneously would leave no one available, violating the continuous on-duty requirement.

(Source: NY 18D Part 487 Adult Homes.pdf, pages 44-46, effective 10/04/2023.)","status":"completed"}
